label: University of Pennsylvania LJS 388: Mulakhkhaṣ fī al-hayʼah
attribution: Provided by the University of Pennsylvania Libraries
description:
Summary: Astronomical textbook whose title translates as Epitome (or Quintessence) of astronomy.
        Language: Arabic
        Support: paper
        Extent: 
        Collation: Paper, i + 19 + ii.
        Layout: Written in 21 long lines.
        Script: Written in nastaʻlīq script.
        Decoration: 4 diagrams in red ink (f. 3v-5r), 1 diagram in black ink (f. 18r); selected words and phrases in red ink.
        Binding: Morocco.
        Origin: Written in Persia, now Iran, dated A.H. 29 Rabīʻ I, 786 (21 May 1384, colophon, f. 19v).
        Cite as:	
        UPenn LJS 388
        For catalog record, see Permanent Link: 5068122 http://hdl.library.upenn.edu/1017/d/medren/5068122
  For TEI description and digital images, see: http://openn.library.upenn.edu/Data/LJSchoenbergManuscripts/html/ljs388.html
